      <p>
        <s t="t1">
          <ot>I am not afraid of tomorrow, for I have seen yesterday and love today.</ot>
          <tt>我不害怕明天，因为我经历过昨天，又热爱今天。</tt>
          <wd v="4">
            <w>
              <txt>be afraid of</txt>
              <pro></pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>害怕</def>
				<clon>
					<c>am</c>
					<c>afraid of</c>
				</clon>
            </w>
          </wd>
        </s>
        <s t="t1">
          <ot>Ａ smile is the shortest distance between two people.</ot>
          <tt>微笑是两人之间最短的距离。</tt>
          <wd v="4">
            <w>
              <txt>shortest distance</txt>
              <pro></pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>最短距离，最近距离 </def>
            </w>
          </wd>
        </s>
        <s t="t1">
          <ot>Whatever with the past has gone, the best is always yet to come.</ot>
          <tt>无论过去发生什么，最好的尚未到来。</tt>
        </s>
        <s t="t1">
          <ot>Hope for the best and prepare for the worst.</ot>
          <tt>从最好处着想， 从最坏处准备。</tt>
          <wd v="4">
            <w>
              <txt>prepare</txt>
              <pro>[pri'pεə]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>vt. 准备；使适合；装备；起草</def>
            </w>
          </wd>
        </s>
        <s t="t1">
          <ot>Sorrow is at parting if at meeting there be laughter.</ot>
          <tt>相见欢时，离别难。</tt>
          <wd v="4">
            <w>
              <txt>sorrow</txt>
              <pro>['sɔrəu]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>n. 悲伤；懊悔；伤心事</def>
            </w>
          </wd>
        </s>
